# Styling notification content

Designing rich notification for Push closely follows the markdown standards. Below is a live example of what is possible with push notifications currently via Push Protocol.


<head>
  <title>Styling Notification Content | Push Notifications | Push Documentation</title>
</head>


## How to design content rich notifications?

```jsx live 
customPropMinimized="true"
customPropHidden="true"

function App(props) {
  const msgPlaceholder = `Hey there!
  
You can do [b:so many things] with [d: Push notifications!]
[i:Send notifications in style] that can also contain [bi: timestamp in epoch but only at the end]

Like how this is the [s: oldest notification] though [t: not really]

You can also create links and <a href="https://github.com/ethereum-push-notification-service/PIPs/tree/main/definitions/Standard/PRC/Notification/Content">checkout how our markdown is evolving here!</a> [timestamp: 837349322]
`;

  const [title, setTitle] = useState('Hello World!');
  const [message, setMessage] = useState(msgPlaceholder);
  const [mediaURL, setMediaURL] = useState('https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=R8nsAhyrvTI');
  const [ctaLink, setCTALink] = useState('https://push.org');

  const titleRef = useRef();
  const messageRef = useRef();
  const mediaURLRef = useRef();
  const ctaLinkRef = useRef();

  useEffect(() => {
    if (titleRef.current) {
      titleRef.current.value = title;
    }

    if (messageRef.current) {
      messageRef.current.value = message;
    }

    if (mediaURLRef.current) {
      mediaURLRef.current.value = mediaURL;
    }

    if (ctaLinkRef.current) {
      ctaLinkRef.current.value = ctaLink;
    }

  }, [title, message, mediaURL, ctaLink]);

  const generatePreview = () => {
    const titleText = titleRef.current.value;
    const messageText = messageRef.current.value;
    const mediaURLText = mediaURLRef.current.value;
    const CTAText = ctaLinkRef.current.value;

    setTitle(titleText);
    setMessage(messageText);
    setMediaURL(mediaURLText);
    setCTALink(CTAText);
  };

  function NotificationInterface() {
    const inputStyle = {
      padding: '10px',
      margin: '10px 0',
      width: '100%',
      boxSizing: 'border-box',
    };

    const textareaStyle = {
      ...inputStyle,
      height: '100px',
      resize: 'vertical',
    };

    const buttonStyle = {
      padding: '10px 20px',
      backgroundColor: '#dd44b9',
      color: '#FFF',
      border: 'none',
      borderRadius: '5px',
      cursor: 'pointer',
      marginTop: '20px',
    };

    return (
      <div style={{ width: 'auto', margin: '20px auto' }}>
        <div style={{ display: 'flex', justifyContent: 'space-between' }}>
          <div style={{ flex: 1 }}>
            <label>Notification Title</label>
            <input 
              type="text" 
              placeholder="Notification Title" 
              style={inputStyle}
              ref={titleRef}
              maxLength={80}
            />
          </div>
        </div>
        <label>Notification Message</label>
        <textarea 
          placeholder="Notification Message" 
          style={textareaStyle}
          maxLength={500}
          ref={messageRef}
        />
        <div style={{ display: 'flex', justifyContent: 'space-between' }}>
          <div style={{ flex: 1, marginRight: '10px' }}>
            <label>Media URL (Optional)</label>
            <input 
              type="text" 
              placeholder="Media URL" 
              style={inputStyle}
              ref={mediaURLRef}
            />
          </div>
          <div style={{ flex: 1, marginLeft: '10px' }}>
            <label>Call to Action URL (Optional)</label>
            <input 
              type="text" 
              placeholder="Call to Action URL" 
              style={inputStyle}
              ref={ctaLinkRef}
            />
          </div>
        </div>
        <button style={buttonStyle} onClick={generatePreview}>Generate Preview</button>

        <p /> 
        <p />
        <h2>Real time notification preview</h2>

        {/* Ideally you will only import this in your code */}
        <NotificationItem
          key='unique_id' // any unique id
          notificationTitle={title}
          notificationBody={message}
          cta={ctaLink}
          image={mediaURL}
          icon={'data:image/png;base64,'}
          app={'Your awesome Channel!!'}
        />
       
      </div>
    );
  }

  return (
    <>
      <NotificationInterface />
    </>
  );
}
```

### Supported markdown
These are some of the styles currently supported by **Push**

| Previous Markdown | Cuurrent Markdown  | Use Case | Styling effects   |
|---|---|---|---|
| `[b: textcontent]`  | `**Bold**`  |  For Emphasis | For Bold  |
| `[i: textcontent]` | `__Italic__`  |  For Emphasis | For Italics  |
| `[bi: textcontent]`  | ` ***Bold&Italics***` | For Emphasis  |  For Bold and Italics |
| `/n`  |  `/n` |  For Segregation | For new line  |
| `[w: textcontent]`  | `<PUSHText color="white">Hello World</PUSHText>` | For colored text  |  For white color |
| - | `<PUSHText color="#ANYHEXCODE"> Hello world </PUSHText>` | For colored text  | Supports any color by hexcode |
| `[d: textcontent]` | `<PUSHText color="primary">Hello World </PUSHText>` | For colored text  | EPNS Primary colored Text  |
| `[s: textcontent]` | `<PUSHText color="secondary">Hello World </PUSHText>` | For colored text  | EPNS Secondary colored Text   |
| `[t: textcontent]` | `<PUSHText color="tertiary">Hello World </PUSHText>` | For colored text  | EPNS Tetiary colored Text  |
| `[u: textcontent]` | `<PUSHText color="green" link="https://www.epns.io"> EPNS website </PUSHText>` | For URLâ€™s | Underlined, Red Colored Text |
| `[ts: timestamp_in_epoch]` | `[ts: timestamp_in_epoch]` | For timestamp | Required to be last component in description of the payload |

### Contribute
We believe notifications or any sort of web3 communication is a community wide effort and we invite everyone to come, discuss and better it for everyone via [Push Improvement Proposals (PIPs)](https://github.com/ethereum-push-notification-service/PIPs "Learn more about Push Improvement Proposals (PIPs)").
